USSD to HTTP
-----------------------------------------

Usage: http://host:port/path?param1=${port}&param2=${message}&param3=${time}&param4=${status}&param5=${code}&param6=${id}&

a Parameter Description

1. host
    Description: HTTP server IP address or domain
    Example: 172.16.6.171 

2. port
    Description: HTTP server's port 
    Example: 80

3. path
    Description: a path of file that Used to receive and handle request of USSD data
    Example: smsreceive.php

4. param1:
    Description: a name of parameter used to handle the value of 'port' 
    Example: port

5. param2
    Description: a name of parameter used to handle the value of 'message'
    Example: message

6. param3
    Description: a name of parameter used to handle the value of 'time'
    Example: time

7. param4
    Description: a name of parameter used to handle the value of 'status'
    Example: status

8. param5
    Description: a name of parameter used to handle the value of 'code'
    Example: code

9. param6
    Description: a name of parameter used to handle the value of 'id'
    Example: id

b Result Description
    Example: 
        Time: 2018/12/29 17:47:34 
        ID: 1234
        Port: 1
        Message: Your blance is 0.00 
        code: 15
        status: 2
		 